column5: Hi Guys Just got back from a week of Muskie fishing with my son . We fished Balsam and Sturgeon lakes boated 18 Muskies saw another 25 from follows , hits and hooked and lost fish . Biggest was 44" most were between 36" and 39" all were healthy and fat except 2 that had sores on them . We caught 2 Tigers on Balsam along with a couple Pike up to 29" also caught several Bass 2-4 lbs on our Muskie lures . We didn't see a Walleye all week we usual see a couple nice ones on our jerk and glide baits . Dad caught the biggest for the week so I won the $10 but then on the way home I bought lunch LOL . I have to wait until spring Striper season for my next fishing fix so everyone good luck with the rest of the season .
Glad ya all had a good trip. Nice fish .
Thanks for sharing. The water just dipped in low sixtys 60-62 seemed to r turn them on on sturgeon was kept busy yesterday without ever losing sight of my house skis were everyehere and hungary
Great stuff! Both are great fish, that tiger looks deadly!
Your son is doing a good job of guiding it seems, letting the old man win the big money!  Glad you had a good trip.
Nice job hank. Glad you guys had a good week.
Good show man! Nice looking fish!
